Sec. 143.001. SUFFICIENT FENCE REQUIRED. Except as provided by
this chapter for an area in which a local option stock law has been
adopted, each gardener or farmer shall make a sufficient fence around
cleared land in cultivation that is at least five feet high and will
prevent hogs from passing through.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1339, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

